other_tests.findings: Reported as adenocarcinoma with papillary features; characterized by pseudopapillary clusters and three-dimensional tubes of tumor cells with scanty cytoplasm and high nuclear:cytoplasmic ratio.
other_tests.changes_over_time: Two subsequent cervical biopsies demonstrated only inflammatory and reactive changes, with no evidence of neoplasia.

other_tests.findings: Demonstrated only shedding and proliferative phase endometrium.
Demonstrated a diploid phenotype of tumor cells.
Revealed an 8.5-cm left ovarian mass, a 3.5-cm right ovary, 75 mL of ascites, and prominent bilateral pelvic lymphadenopathy.

other_tests.procedure_name: Touch preparations of the left ovarian tumor
other_tests.findings: Showed central cores of acellular hyaline material surrounded by cells with cytologic features similar to those in peritoneal washings.
